description: Dan speaks of the wonderful Chicago pianist, writer, and enthusiastic advocate Art Hodes from a conversation on Fifty-Second Street in the late Forties onwards to Chicago and television programs with Hodes, Pee Wee Russell, Jimmy McPartland, and Wild Bill Davison (with memories of Frank Teschemacher's death), bassist Truck Parham, and Lester Young, jamming with Hodes --- a record date scuttled by Leonard Feather.  Recorded by Michael Steinman for JAZZ LIVES (http://www.jazzlives.wordpress.com).
